Qtpl is template library for use in CGI applications. It's :
	- support blocks;
	- support simple variable and array substitutions;
	- handle simple logic (IF, ELSE, ENDIF). More complex logic must
		still in your program.

It's first public release of library. Refer to module inline documentation.
Some examples stored in ./ex directory. 

Also check http://qtpl.sourceforge.net/

HISTORY:
	0.1. Basic syntax from XTemlate (xtpl.sourceforge.net). Porting it
		to Perl. 

	0.2. Some syntax addons, such as IF blocks, blocks saving parsing
		order (main.row:block1).
